President Muhammadu Buhari on Monday wrote President Xi Jinping of China saying he was delighted that the bond of friendship between Nigeria and China has continued to strengthen.
The President wrote to felicitate with the Chinese leader on the occasion of the 71st Anniversary of the proclamation of the Republic of China, and the country’s National Day. Buhari said though COVID-19 pandemic has caused disruptions in the economies of the world, he was glad that Nigeria and China have remained steadfast, and supported each other.” President Buhari appreciated the government of China for being supportive of the infrastructural revolution in Nigeria. A copy of the letter made available to DAILY POST on Monday by Femi Adesina, his spokesman, said the President commended the Chinese government for being very helpful in the realisation of the developmental agenda of Africa. See original letter attached <img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter wp-image-843812 size-large" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Screenshot_20200928-165003_Gmail-498x1024.jpg" alt="" width="498" height="1024" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Screenshot_20200928-165003_Gmail-498x1024.jpg 498w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Screenshot_20200928-165003_Gmail-146x300.jpg 146w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Screenshot_20200928-165003_Gmail.jpg 720w" sizes="(max-width: 498px) 100vw, 498px"> <img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter wp-image-843813 size-large" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Screenshot_20200928-165017_Gmail-498x1024.jpg" alt="" width="498" height="1024" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Screenshot_20200928-165017_Gmail-498x1024.jpg 498w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Screenshot_20200928-165017_Gmail-146x300.jpg 146w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Screenshot_20200928-165017_Gmail.jpg 720w" sizes="(max-width: 498px) 100vw, 498px">